{"files":{"tech_short_warpGate1.md":"A breakthrough in hyperspace navigation, the warp gate provides ships with pre-calculated navigations allowing them to travel between warp gates twice as fast as normal.","diplomacy_draske_greeting_0_2.md":"Think carefully before speaking.\n","tech_short_gaussTurret1.md":"A rapid fire ballistic turret which utilized massive electromagnetic energy to drive titanium alloy, armor piercing projectiles at enemy ships.  Armor piercing weapons completely ignore the targets armor.","leader_short_hanifer.md":"**Ship:** 20% damage resistance and reduced speed loss from structure damage\n**Fleet:** 5% damage resistance\n**Ultimate:** Hanifer's iron will and determination will allow his ship to survive until the last ship in his fleet has fallen\n\nSome people are forged over a lifetime.  Others, like Colonel Hanifer, are forged in a single moment.  When the Coalition Navy first fought its first extra solar battle it felt confident of victory.  The battle became known as the Hopeless Battle of Proximo Prime, and Colonel Hanifer’s battered, torn ship was the only vessel to return.  And he was the only survivor.\n\nThe Colonel’s resilience and tenacity brought him instant recognition from every human world.  But none of it could heal his inner survivor’s guilt.  Determined that a human fleet will never again be defeated in battle he used personal knowledge of battle-damage to honeycomb his ships with hatches and cross braces, increasing their damage resistance in general combat.  Ready for action, he will fight till the very last breath is blasted out of his body.","diplomacy_cyban_disappointed_2_1.md":"Our projections will need to be adjusted to account for this change.\n","diplomacy_isather_request_2_1.md":"Our pact may benefit from this.\n","diplomacy_vass_disappointed_2_1.md":"The Collective will find ways to make up for this loss.\n","diplomacy_vass_request_3_2.md":"Yes, friend.  The Vass will Ponder it.\n","tech_short_advancedCityPlanning2.md":"Advances in city planning provides additional space for more population. Increases maximum colony population by 4.","diplomacy_human_happy_1_1.md":"The Confederation could use that.\n","race_short_richHomeworld.md":"Race begins the game with a mineral rich homeworld.","UNEXPLORED_STAR1.md":"Class B stars very luminous, very energetic blue stars. Similar to class O stars, they tend to burn through their hydrogen very quicky and live for a relatively short period of time. Similar to class O stars, class B stars are unlikely to have many planets.","diplomacy_vass_request_0_2.md":"Only if it truly favors the Vass…\n","diplomacy_human_war_0_2.md":"The time for negotiations has passed.  The time for action is now!\n","diplomacy_cyban_happy_2_1.md":"The Community thanks you for your gift.\n","UNEXPLORED_STAR19.md":"Class K stars have the best chance of containing habitable planets, but those planets are often poor in mineral resources. Habitable planets in binary systems often take advantage of the increased radiation exposure to provide a more fertaile environment.","diplomacy_isather_happy_2_2.md":"We will honor your gift .\n","diplomacy_cyban_greeting_2_1.md":"By the bonds of our treaty, you may speak.\n","diplomacy_isather_disappointed_0_1.md":"This will prove to be a mistake for you.\n","tech_short_improvedStarDrive3.md":"Using careful experimentation and exhaustive testing procedures, scientists can refine the star drive to the point that your ships can travel 7 parsecs each turn.","diplomacy_taku_disappointed_1_1.md":"Fly softly, lest this lead to turbulent skies.\n","diplomacy_uggathaaa_request_3_0.md":"Swift wings will carry your request.\n","tech_short_energyShields3.md":"Advances in this technology allow for more incoming enemy munitions to be blocked. Limit one per ship.","diplomacy_taku_greeting_2_3.md":"Will you fly with us now?\n","diplomacy_human_disappointed_3_0.md":"Your decision is devastatingly disappointing.\n","diplomacy_isather_happy_2_1.md":